Although there are no direct flights to the UK, there are now options for returning indirectly, including via Barbados, Miami and Toronto.
Some commercial flights have now commenced or resumed service from Argyle International Airport in St Vincent. In terms of regional flights, Fly One Caribbean, SVG Air and Caribbean Airlines all now offer a flight service to Barbados. Weekly international flights are also operating from St Vincent to Miami with American Airlines and Toronto (Air Canada). British Airways has also now resumed a limited flight schedule from Barbados to London.
You should consult FCO Travel Advice for requirements for entry and onward travel in other countries on your route.
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British High Commission Bridgetown on + 1 246 430 7800.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission on Facebook and Twitter.
